data.text:
Plot[]

Grant is cornered by Peggy and has to come clean about the wine bar deal with George. Peggy later confronts George. Roy is on the warpath about Manor Wood and refuses to hand over the money he owes to Frank. Phil has got the hump with Ricky. Sanjay confronts Terry and is told that Neelam has sold the business to him. Louise and Terry have a slanging match. An upset Louise heads for the Vic and informs Grant that Tiffany wants her passport. He asks Louise to give the wine bar a once over with him. Barry in a fit of conscience tries to clear the air with Ian about the Cindy escapade and his part in it. Jimmy wants to quit reading and writing lessons but Sarah and Alex attempt to talk him out of it. Ricky sees Frank is upset about losing his money supply and accuses Peggy of blabbing about Manor Wood. Peggy slings him out of the Vic. Tony tries sending a note to Teresa but Gianni intercepts it. Peggy offers to be Frank's business partner.
